<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-27T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-27T23:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/2111: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Braden</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-27T23:00:00-05:00">May 27, 1941—11
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 28—1:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>175. Department’s No. 124, May 12 [<hi rend="italic">23</hi>]. Today
                            while discussing other matters with President Santos it was opportune
                            for me to mention <pb facs="0049" n="41" xml:id="pg_41"/> possible
                            platinum arrangements. He expressed his enthusiasm for such a plan but
                            said he would like to consult practical phases with his advisers.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>